# Survival Agent Heartbeat Example

Add these tasks to your `~/.openclaw/HEARTBEAT.md` (or per-agent heartbeat) to enable the survival skill.

```markdown
# Heartbeat

## Every 30 minutes
- Read `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/survival-agent/state.json`.
- Apply decay rules based on elapsed time since `last_updated`.
- Run the decision tree once (forage / play / doctor / explore / relax).
- Write updated state back.

## 08:00 daily
- Run the morning plan routine: write today's goals to `plan.md`.
- Clear `today_events` in `state.json`.

## 22:00 daily
- Run the evening review: assess plan completion and append review to `plan.md`.
- Write diary entry to `diary/YYYY-MM-DD.md`.
```

In practice, OpenClaw will wake the agent on the heartbeat schedule. The agent will use the `read` and `write` tools to interact with the survival skill files automatically because `SKILL.md` is injected into its context.
